notices.description:
Description

Get different output when using command: "tmsh show running one-line" for:
User role - Admin
User role - Audit
An example for differentiation between Admin and Auditor role:
diff f5-admin f5-auditor
---  f5-admin ---
< sys folder / { device-group Common/Sync-failover inherited-devicegroup false inherited-traffic-group false traffic-group Common/traffic-group-1 }
< sys folder Common { device-group Common/Sync-failover inherited-devicegroup true inherited-traffic-group true traffic-group Common/traffic-group-1 }
< sys folder Common/Drafts { device-group Common/Sync-failover inherited-devicegroup true inherited-traffic-group true traffic-group Common/traffic-group-1 }
< sys folder Pci { device-group Common/Sync-failover inherited-devicegroup true inherited-traffic-group true traffic-group Common/traffic-group-1 }
--- f5-auditor ---
> sys folder / { inherited-devicegroup false inherited-traffic-group false }
> sys folder Common { inherited-devicegroup true inherited-traffic-group true }
> sys folder Common/Drafts { inherited-devicegroup true inherited-traffic-group true }
> sys folder Pci { inherited-devicegroup true inherited-traffic-group true }
